reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for craft shows
reviews.reviewText: This table is great for a quick and easy set-up and break-down. The table top is hard molded plastic, and the black color hides dirt and scratches well. It also blends in to the stretchable black tablecloth very well for a professional appearance. The table legs are sturdy black powder-coated pipe steel. They are slightly on the stiff side, but this also means that the table won't easily collapse. The table assembles very easily. Releasing the catches and two quick, firm knocks is all it takes to break down the table. I'm very happy with this table and know I'll be getting a lot of use out of it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Strong, portable and fits my space
reviews.reviewText: I needed a rectangular project table that would fit across my 62.5” wide hearth and snugly against the fireplace wall (we don’t use the fireplace). The leg span of a 6’ table we have is too short to fit over the hearth. The span of the legs on this 8’ table is 78.5” - so I now have (even more) surface and it fits the space perfectly. Plus it will be handy for outside parties. The handle on one side and grip space on the other makes it easy to move, plus it folds in half for storage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great product, but won’t order on line again
reviews.reviewText: I have had several Cosco tables in the past and loved them. I just returned my THIRD table due (ordered on line,) due to damage & a gauge in the middle of the table. I really like these tables and not sure where the problem is originating from. In 2 instances, the boxes were damaged, and the table. In the 3rd instance, box was fine, but table had damage. I actually kept one table that was a replacement for one that ended up at the incorrect address. Small amount of damage, but not super noticeable. I’ll be using these for crafts/sewing. I will continue to use this product, but won’t order on-line anymore unfortunately. For how much these tables cost, I will buy in local stores. Again, GREAT product, but somewhere there is a huge problem from assembly line to delivery!

reviews.reviewTitle: Lightweight and great look for a folding table
reviews.reviewText: Really happy with this, set it up downstairs for a project/hobby table, and it's long enough that several people can work simultaneously on things. Nicely open beneath to allow legs as people sit there (vs. some folding tables you can find). The white color is great as it allows small objects to be easily seen (not sure if the black surface would be as good in that regard). I don't see myself folding this up anytime soon, but if I needed to it's nice to know that I could fold it away for storage.Half a star off for the fact that the white color (which I got) is more expensive than the black. Seriously, basic colors shouldn't be hard to supply or worth a price difference...

I use this when working on vehicles to place parts ect. Sturdy and easily folds, kind of on the heavy side but it’s sturdy. Not too heavy. Thick plastic. Folds up nicely when not used just keep the box. Mine is black so I kept the box for when storing. I’m happy about this purchase.

Table is sturdy and simple to set up. Folds up nicely to half its size (4ft) making it easy to store. Needed customer support and Amazon did an outstanding job at addressing my concerns. Would not hesitate to buy again.

This is exactly what i was looking for when i searched up “folding table” it is very compact & easy to store, great quality & it comes pre built which is a huge bonus. The only downside i would have to mention is the weight, as a fit younger man I thought this would have been easier to carry with the handle but it is not.. it is quite hefty but well worth every penny.
Perfect for our gathering and easy to set up and take down. Very sturdy
